Each substrate was assessed for conversion with two enzymes (\pfomt wild-type and 4'-specific variant \pfomt Y51R N202W) at four different conditions.
Magnesium addition and pH for the different conditions (pH/\cf{Mg^2+}: low/no, low/yes, high/no, high/yes).
The ``low'' and ``high'' pH-values were 7.5 and 8.6, respectively.
When \cf{Mg^2+} was added the concentration was \SI{10}{\milli\molar}.
The reactions were incubated at \degC{30} for 16\,h (see section \ref{sec:omtassay}).
